Application Deploymet with CI/CD Jenkins on Kubernetes AWS EKS using  ArgoCd.

-	Source code and configuration is managed at GitHub for code, dependencies, application manifests and respective Jenkins file with stages and Docker file.
-	Using GitHub for source code  CI/CD pipeline implemented in two stages Continuous Integration with Jenkins and Continuous Deployment using Argocd on Kubernetes or AWS EKS.

-	Continuous integration involves :
-	Source code checkout at GitHub repository 
-	Application Build using Maven 
-	Static Code analysis using SonarQube for code scanning
(Note: SonarQube Server to be configured and credentials and need to be added in Jenkins)
-	Using Docker for image build for application and pushing it to Docker-hub maintained repository.
(Docker credentials need to be configured with Jenkins including GitHub credentials)

-	 Continuous Deployment using ArgoCD:
-	ArgoCd operator Installed at AWS EKS
-	Tracks the application manifest at GitHub
-	Any commit happens at repository ArgoCd track the changes
-	Updated application manifest deployed on AWS EKS using ArgoCd.


